312    private function generate_post_title($listing) {
313        $address = sanitize_text_field($listing['UnparsedAddress']);
314        $city = isset($listing['City']) ? sanitize_text_field($listing['City']) : '';
315        $province = isset($listing['StateOrProvince']) ? sanitize_text_field($listing['StateOrProvince']) : '';
316
317        $title_parts = array($address);
318        if (!empty($city)) {

320        }
321        if (!empty($province)) {
322            $title_parts[] = $province;
323        }

325        return implode(', ', $title_parts);
326    }

328    /**

401    /**
402     * Update post content with image placeholders after images are processed
403     *
404     * @since 1.0.0
405     * @param int $post_id Post ID
406     * @return void
407     */
408    private function update_post_content_with_images($post_id) {
409        $post_content = get_post_field('post_content', $post_id);
410        
411        // Get all image URLs for this post
412        $image_urls = $this->get_listing_image_urls($post_id);
413        
414        // Replace universal image placeholders
415        $post_content = str_replace('<!-- LISTING_IMAGES_PLACEHOLDER -->', implode(',', $image_urls), $post_content);
416        
417        // Replace base64 encoded image URLs (for Visual Composer compatibility)
418        $base64_images = $this->get_base64_encoded_images($image_urls);
419        $post_content = str_replace('<!-- BASE64IMAGES_PLACEHOLDER -->', $base64_images, $post_content);
420        
421        // Replace individual image placeholders (1-10)
422        for ($i = 1; $i <= 10; $i++) {
423            $image_url = isset($image_urls[$i - 1]) ? $image_urls[$i - 1] : '';
424            $post_content = str_replace("<!-- LISTING_IMAGE_{$i}_PLACEHOLDER -->", $image_url, $post_content);
425        }
426        
427        // Replace WordPress native placeholders
428        $featured_image_html = $this->get_featured_image_html($post_id);
429        $gallery_html = $this->get_image_gallery_html($post_id);
430        
431        $post_content = str_replace('<!-- FEATURED_IMAGE_PLACEHOLDER -->', $featured_image_html, $post_content);
432        $post_content = str_replace('<!-- IMAGE_GALLERY_PLACEHOLDER -->', $gallery_html, $post_content);
433        
434        
435        // Update the post content
436        wp_update_post(array(
437            'ID' => $post_id,
438            'post_content' => $post_content
439        ));
440    }

622    /**
623     * Sanitize meta value based on data type
624     *
625     * @since 1.2.0
626     * @param mixed $value Raw value from API
627     * @param string $type Sanitization type
628     * @return mixed Sanitized value
629     */
630    private function sanitize_meta_value($value, $type) {
631        if ($value === null || $value === '') {
632            return '';
633        }
634        
635        switch ($type) {
636            case 'text':
637                return sanitize_text_field($value);
638                
639            case 'textarea':
640                return sanitize_textarea_field($value);
641                
642            case 'url':
643                return esc_url_raw($value);
644                
645            case 'int':
646                return intval($value);
647                
648            case 'float':
649                return floatval($value);
650                
651            case 'boolean':
652                // Handle various boolean representations from API
653                if (is_bool($value)) {
654                    return $value ? '1' : '0';
655                }
656                $value = strtolower(trim($value));
657                return in_array($value, array('true', '1', 'yes', 'y'), true) ? '1' : '0';
658                
659            case 'datetime':
660                // Ensure datetime is in MySQL format
661                $timestamp = strtotime($value);
662                return $timestamp ? gmdate('Y-m-d H:i:s', $timestamp) : '';
663                
664            default:
665                return sanitize_text_field($value);
666        }
667    }
668
669    /**
670     * Calculate price per square foot
671     *
672     * @since 1.2.0
673     * @param array $listing Listing data
674     * @return float Price per square foot or 0 if cannot calculate
675     */
676    private function calculate_price_per_sqft($listing) {
677        $price = isset($listing['ListPrice']) ? floatval($listing['ListPrice']) : 0;
678        $sqft = isset($listing['LivingArea']) ? floatval($listing['LivingArea']) : 0;
679        
680        if ($price > 0 && $sqft > 0) {
681            return round($price / $sqft, 2);
682        }
683        
684        return 0;
685    }

687    /**
688     * Calculate days on market
689     *
690     * @since 1.2.0
691     * @param array $listing Listing data
692     * @return int Days on market or 0 if cannot calculate
693     */
694    private function calculate_days_on_market($listing) {
695        $on_market_date = isset($listing['OnMarketDate']) ? $listing['OnMarketDate'] : 
696                         (isset($listing['ListingContractDate']) ? $listing['ListingContractDate'] : '');
697        
698        if (empty($on_market_date)) {
699            return 0;
700        }
701        
702        $market_timestamp = strtotime($on_market_date);
703        if (!$market_timestamp) {
704            return 0;
705        }
706        
707        return max(0, floor((time() - $market_timestamp) / (24 * 60 * 60)));
708    }

758    /**
759     * Process listing images using AMPRE Media API
760     * 
761     * Best Practice: Single-process import for atomic operations and immediate user experience
762     *
763     * @since 1.0.0
764     * @param int $post_id Post ID
765     * @param array $listing Listing data
766     * @return array Statistics about image processing
767     */
768    private function process_listing_images($post_id, $listing) {
769        $mls_number = sanitize_text_field($listing['ListingKey']);
770        $stats = array(
771            'total' => 0,
772            'downloaded' => 0,
773            'failed' => 0,
774            'featured_set' => false
775        );
776        
777        // Get media from AMPRE API
778        if (defined('WP_CLI') && WP_CLI) {
779            WP_CLI::line("  Fetching media for MLS {$mls_number}...");
780        }
781        
782        require_once SHIFT8_TREB_PLUGIN_DIR . 'includes/class-shift8-treb-ampre-service.php';
783        $ampre_service = new Shift8_TREB_AMPRE_Service($this->settings);
784        
785        $media_items = $ampre_service->get_media_for_listing($mls_number);
786        
787        if (is_wp_error($media_items) || empty($media_items)) {
788            if (defined('WP_CLI') && WP_CLI) {
789                WP_CLI::line("  No media found for MLS {$mls_number}");
790            }
791            shift8_treb_log('No media found for listing', array(
792                'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
793                'error' => is_wp_error($media_items) ? $media_items->get_error_message() : 'No media items'
794            ));
795            return $stats;
796        }
797
798        $stats['total'] = count($media_items);
799        
800        if (defined('WP_CLI') && WP_CLI) {
801            WP_CLI::line("  Found {$stats['total']} images for MLS {$mls_number}");
802        }
803        
804        shift8_treb_log('Processing listing images', array(
805            'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
806            'image_count' => $stats['total']
807        ));
808
809        $featured_image_set = false;
810        $preferred_image_id = null;
811        $first_successful_image = null;
812
813        // Performance: Allow unlimited images by default, but provide filter for hosting constraints
814        // Following .cursorrules performanceOptimizationPatterns: make expensive operations conditional
815        $original_count = count($media_items);
816        $max_images = apply_filters('shift8_treb_max_images_per_listing', 0); // 0 = unlimited
817        if ($max_images > 0) {
818            $media_items = array_slice($media_items, 0, $max_images);
819            shift8_treb_log('Limited images per listing', array(
820                'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
821                'original_count' => $original_count,
822                'limited_count' => count($media_items),
823                'max_images' => $max_images
824            ));
825        }
826
827        // Performance: Check processing mode
828        // Following .cursorrules performanceOptimizationPatterns: batch processing default for better performance
829        $skip_images = isset($this->settings['skip_image_download']) && $this->settings['skip_image_download'];
830        $batch_mode = !isset($this->settings['batch_image_processing']) || $this->settings['batch_image_processing']; // Default: true
831        
832        if ($skip_images) {
833            shift8_treb_log('Skipping image download for fast sync', array(
834                'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
835            ));
836            
837            // Store external references only
838            foreach ($media_items as $index => $media) {
839                if (isset($media['MediaURL']) && !empty($media['MediaURL'])) {
840                    $is_preferred = isset($media['PreferredPhotoYN']) && $media['PreferredPhotoYN'] === true;
841                    $this->store_external_image_reference($post_id, $media['MediaURL'], $mls_number, $index + 1, $is_preferred);
842                }
843            }
844            return $stats;
845        }
846
847        // Batch processing mode for better performance
848        if ($batch_mode) {
849            if (defined('WP_CLI') && WP_CLI) {
850                WP_CLI::line("  Starting batch download for MLS {$mls_number}...");
851            }
852            return $this->process_images_batch($post_id, $media_items, $mls_number, $stats);
853        }
854
855        foreach ($media_items as $index => $media) {
856            if (!isset($media['MediaURL']) || empty($media['MediaURL'])) {
857                continue;
858            }
859
860            $image_url = esc_url_raw($media['MediaURL']);
861            $is_preferred = isset($media['PreferredPhotoYN']) && $media['PreferredPhotoYN'] === true;
862            
863            // Best Practice: Download with retry and fallback to external URL
864            $attachment_id = $this->download_and_attach_image_with_retry($image_url, $post_id, $mls_number, $index + 1);
865
866            if ($attachment_id) {
867                $stats['downloaded']++;
868                
869                // Track first successful image as fallback
870                if (!$first_successful_image) {
871                    $first_successful_image = $attachment_id;
872                }
873                
874                // Track preferred image for featured image (highest priority)
875                if ($is_preferred) {
876                    $preferred_image_id = $attachment_id;
877                }
878            } else {
879                $stats['failed']++;
880                
881                // Fallback: Store external URL for future retry or display
882                $this->store_external_image_reference($post_id, $image_url, $mls_number, $index + 1, $is_preferred);
883                
884                shift8_treb_log('Image download failed, stored external reference', array(
885                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
886                    'image_url' => esc_html($image_url),
887                    'index' => $index
888                ));
889            }
890        }
891
892        // Featured image priority logic:
893        // 1. First image (image_number = 1) - ALWAYS gets priority for consistency
894        // 2. Preferred image (PreferredPhotoYN = true) - secondary priority
895        // 3. First successfully downloaded image - fallback
896        
897        // Find the first image (image_number = 1) if it was successfully downloaded
898        $first_image_id = null;
899        foreach ($media_items as $index => $media) {
900            if (($index + 1) == 1) { // First image
901                $existing_attachment = $this->get_existing_attachment($mls_number, 1);
902                if ($existing_attachment) {
903                    $first_image_id = $existing_attachment;
904                } elseif ($first_successful_image && ($index + 1) == 1) {
905                    $first_image_id = $first_successful_image;
906                }
907                break;
908            }
909        }
910        
911        // Set featured image with priority: First image > Preferred > First successful
912        $featured_image_id = $first_image_id ?: ($preferred_image_id ?: $first_successful_image);
913        
914        if ($featured_image_id) {
915            set_post_thumbnail($post_id, $featured_image_id);
916            $stats['featured_set'] = true;
917            
918            $priority_type = $first_image_id ? 'first_image' : ($preferred_image_id ? 'preferred' : 'first_successful');
919            
920            shift8_treb_log('Set featured image', array(
921                'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
922                'attachment_id' => $featured_image_id,
923                'priority_type' => $priority_type
924            ));
925        }
926
927        // Log final statistics
928        shift8_treb_log('Image processing completed', array(
929            'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
930            'stats' => $stats
931        ));
932
933        return $stats;
934    }

936    /**
937     * Download and attach image to post with enhanced error handling
938     * 
939     * Best Practice: Robust download with proper validation and cleanup
940     *
941     * @since 1.0.0
942     * @param string $image_url Image URL
943     * @param int $post_id Post ID
944     * @param string $mls_number MLS number
945     * @param int $image_number Image number
946     * @return int|false Attachment ID on success, false on failure
947     */
948    private function download_and_attach_image($image_url, $post_id, $mls_number, $image_number) {
949        try {
950            // Best Practice: Validate URL before attempting download
951            if (!filter_var($image_url, FILTER_VALIDATE_URL)) {
952                shift8_treb_log('Invalid image URL', array(
953                    'url' => esc_html($image_url),
954                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
955                ));
956                return false;
957            }
958
959            // Best Practice: Check if image already exists to avoid duplicates
960            $existing_attachment = $this->get_existing_attachment($mls_number, $image_number);
961            if ($existing_attachment) {
962                return $existing_attachment;
963            }
964
965            // Performance: Optimized download settings with faster timeout
966            $response = wp_remote_get($image_url, array(
967                'timeout' => 10, // Reduced from 30 to 10 seconds
968                'user-agent' => 'WordPress/TREB-Plugin',
969                'headers' => array(
970                    'Accept' => 'image/*'
971                ),
972                'sslverify' => false // Skip SSL verification for speed (external images)
973            ));
974            
975            if (is_wp_error($response)) {
976                shift8_treb_log('Image download failed', array(
977                    'url' => esc_html($image_url),
978                    'error' => $response->get_error_message(),
979                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
980                ));
981                return false;
982            }
983
984            $response_code = wp_remote_retrieve_response_code($response);
985            if ($response_code !== 200) {
986                shift8_treb_log('Image download HTTP error', array(
987                    'url' => esc_html($image_url),
988                    'response_code' => $response_code,
989                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
990                ));
991                return false;
992            }
993
994            $image_data = wp_remote_retrieve_body($response);
995            if (empty($image_data)) {
996                return false;
997            }
998
999            // Best Practice: Validate image data
1000            $image_size = strlen($image_data);
1001            if ($image_size < 1024) { // Less than 1KB is likely not a valid image
1002                shift8_treb_log('Image too small', array(
1003                    'url' => esc_html($image_url),
1004                    'size' => $image_size,
1005                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
1006                ));
1007                return false;
1008            }
1009
1010            // Best Practice: Determine file extension from content type
1011            $content_type = wp_remote_retrieve_header($response, 'content-type');
1012            $extension = $this->get_file_extension_from_content_type($content_type);
1013            
1014            // Prepare filename with proper extension
1015            $filename = sanitize_file_name($mls_number . '_' . $image_number . '.' . $extension);
1016            
1017            // Upload to WordPress media library
1018            $upload = wp_upload_bits($filename, null, $image_data);
1019            
1020            if ($upload['error']) {
1021                shift8_treb_log('WordPress upload failed', array(
1022                    'error' => $upload['error'],
1023                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
1024                    'filename' => esc_html($filename)
1025                ));
1026                return false;
1027            }
1028
1029            // Create attachment with proper metadata
1030            $attachment = array(
1031                'post_mime_type' => $content_type ?: 'image/jpeg',
1032                'post_title' => sanitize_text_field($mls_number . ' - Photo ' . $image_number),
1033                'post_content' => '',
1034                'post_status' => 'inherit',
1035                'post_excerpt' => sanitize_text_field('Property photo for MLS ' . $mls_number)
1036            );
1037
1038            $attachment_id = wp_insert_attachment($attachment, $upload['file'], $post_id);
1039
1040            if (is_wp_error($attachment_id)) {
1041                // Clean up uploaded file if attachment creation fails
1042                if (file_exists($upload['file'])) {
1043                    wp_delete_file($upload['file']);
1044                }
1045                shift8_treb_log('Attachment creation failed', array(
1046                    'error' => esc_html($attachment_id->get_error_message()),
1047                    'post_id' => $post_id,
1048                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
1049                    'image_number' => $image_number
1050                ), 'error');
1051                return false;
1052            }
1053
1054            // Verify post_parent was set correctly (debugging for post_parent issue)
1055            $created_attachment = get_post($attachment_id);
1056            if ($created_attachment && $created_attachment->post_parent != $post_id) {
1057                shift8_treb_log('Post parent mismatch detected', array(
1058                    'attachment_id' => $attachment_id,
1059                    'expected_parent' => $post_id,
1060                    'actual_parent' => $created_attachment->post_parent,
1061                    'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
1062                    'image_number' => $image_number
1063                ), 'warning');
1064                
1065                // Attempt to fix the post_parent
1066                wp_update_post(array(
1067                    'ID' => $attachment_id,
1068                    'post_parent' => $post_id
1069                ));
1070            }
1071
1072            // Generate attachment metadata (thumbnails, etc.)
1073            if (!function_exists('wp_generate_attachment_metadata')) {
1074                require_once(ABSPATH . 'wp-admin/includes/image.php');
1075            }
1076            
1077            $attachment_data = wp_generate_attachment_metadata($attachment_id, $upload['file']);
1078            wp_update_attachment_metadata($attachment_id, $attachment_data);
1079
1080            // Best Practice: Add custom meta for easier management
1081            update_post_meta($attachment_id, '_treb_mls_number', sanitize_text_field($mls_number));
1082            update_post_meta($attachment_id, '_treb_image_number', intval($image_number));
1083            update_post_meta($attachment_id, '_treb_source_url', esc_url_raw($image_url));
1084
1085            shift8_treb_log('Image downloaded successfully', array(
1086                'attachment_id' => $attachment_id,
1087                'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number),
1088                'image_number' => $image_number,
1089                'file_size' => $image_size
1090            ));
1091
1092            return $attachment_id;
1093
1094        } catch (Exception $e) {
1095            shift8_treb_log('Image download exception', array(
1096                'url' => esc_html($image_url),
1097                'error' => esc_html($e->getMessage()),
1098                'mls_number' => esc_html($mls_number)
1099            ));
1100            return false;
1101        }
1102    }
1103
1104    /**
1105     * Get existing attachment for MLS listing image
1106     *
1107     * @since 1.0.0
1108     * @param string $mls_number MLS number
1109     * @param int $image_number Image number
1110     * @return int|false Attachment ID if exists, false otherwise
1111     */
1112    private function get_existing_attachment($mls_number, $image_number) {
1113        $existing = get_posts(array(
1114            'post_type' => 'attachment',
1115            'meta_query' => array(
1116                array(
1117                    'key' => '_treb_mls_number',
1118                    'value' => sanitize_text_field($mls_number),
1119                    'compare' => '='
1120                ),
1121                array(
1122                    'key' => '_treb_image_number',
1123                    'value' => intval($image_number),
1124                    'compare' => '='
1125                )
1126            ),
1127            'posts_per_page' => 1,
1128            'fields' => 'ids'
1129        ));
1130
1131        return !empty($existing) ? $existing[0] : false;
1132    }
1133
1134    /**
1135     * Get file extension from content type
1136     *
1137     * @since 1.0.0
1138     * @param string $content_type Content type header
1139     * @return string File extension
1140     */
1141    private function get_file_extension_from_content_type($content_type) {
1142        $mime_to_ext = array(
1143            'image/jpeg' => 'jpg',
1144            'image/jpg' => 'jpg',

1394    /**
1395     * Execute batch HTTP requests using WordPress HTTP API
1396     * 
1397     * Performance: Uses wp_remote_request with concurrent processing where possible
1398     *
1399     * @since 1.0.0
1400     * @param array $batch_requests Array of request configurations
1401     * @return array Array of responses with metadata
1402     */
1403    private function execute_batch_http_requests($batch_requests) {
1404        $responses = array();
1405        
1406        // Cross-hosting compatibility: Adaptive batch sizing based on environment
1407        // Following .cursorrules performanceOptimizationPatterns for hosting environment compatibility
1408        $batch_size = $this->get_optimal_batch_size();
1409        $timeout = $this->get_optimal_timeout();
1410        $delay = $this->get_optimal_delay();
1411        
1412        $batches = array_chunk($batch_requests, $batch_size);
1413        
1414        shift8_treb_log('Starting batch image processing', array(

1418            'timeout' => $timeout,
1419            'delay_ms' => $delay * 1000
1420        ));
1421        
1422        foreach ($batches as $batch_index => $batch) {
1423            $batch_start = microtime(true);
1424            
1425            if (defined('WP_CLI') && WP_CLI && count($batches) > 1) {
1426                WP_CLI::line("    Batch " . ($batch_index + 1) . "/" . count($batches) . " (" . count($batch) . " images)");

1430            foreach ($batch as $request_data) {
1431                // Override timeout in request settings for cross-hosting compatibility
1432                $request_data['request']['timeout'] = $timeout;
1433                
1434                $response = wp_remote_get($request_data['url'], $request_data['request']);
1435                
1436                $responses[] = array(
1437                    'url' => $request_data['url'],
1438                    'index' => $request_data['index'],
1439                    'image_number' => $request_data['image_number'],
1440                    'is_preferred' => $request_data['is_preferred'],
1441                    'response' => $response
1442                );
1443            }
1444            
1445            $batch_time = microtime(true) - $batch_start;
1446            
1447            // Adaptive delay based on batch performance and hosting constraints
1448            if ($batch_index < count($batches) - 1) {
1449                $adaptive_delay = max($delay, $batch_time * 0.1); // At least 10% of batch time
1450                usleep($adaptive_delay * 1000000); // Convert to microseconds
1451            }
1452            
1453            shift8_treb_log('Batch completed', array(

1457            ));
1458        }
1459        
1460        return $responses;
1461    }

1832    /**
1833     * Parse address into components
1834     *
1835     * @since 1.0.0
1836     * @param string $address Full address string
1837     * @return array Address components
1838     */
1839    private function parse_address($address) {
1840        $parts = array(
1841            'number' => '',
1842            'street' => '',
1843            'unit' => ''
1844        );
1845
1846        if (empty($address)) {
1847            return $parts;
1848        }
1849
1850        // Basic address parsing - can be enhanced later
1851        $address = trim($address);
1852        
1853        // Extract unit number (look for patterns like "Unit 123", "Apt 456", "#789")
1854        if (preg_match('/(?:Unit|Apt|Suite|#)\s*([A-Za-z0-9]+)/i', $address, $matches)) {
1855            $parts['unit'] = $matches[1];
1856            $address = preg_replace('/(?:Unit|Apt|Suite|#)\s*[A-Za-z0-9]+/i', '', $address);
1857        }
1858
1859        // Extract street number (first number in the address)
1860        if (preg_match('/^(\d+)/', trim($address), $matches)) {
1861            $parts['number'] = $matches[1];
1862            $address = preg_replace('/^\d+\s*/', '', $address);
1863        }
1864
1865        // Remaining is street name (clean up extra spaces and commas)
1866        $parts['street'] = trim(preg_replace('/,.*$/', '', $address));
1867
1868        return $parts;
1869    }

1992    /**
1993     * Geocode address using Google Maps API
1994     *
1995     * @since 1.0.0
1996     * @param string $address Address to geocode
1997     * @return array|false Array with 'lat' and 'lng' keys, or false on failure
1998     */
1999    private function geocode_address($address) {
2000        // Check if Google Maps API key is configured
2001        if (empty($this->settings['google_maps_api_key'])) {
2002            return false;
2003        }
2004
2005        // Check cache first (to avoid repeated API calls for same address)
2006        $cache_key = 'treb_geocode_' . md5($address);
2007        $cached_result = get_transient($cache_key);
2008        if ($cached_result !== false) {
2009            return $cached_result;
2010        }
2011
2012        // Make geocoding request
2013        $api_key = $this->settings['google_maps_api_key'];
2014        $encoded_address = urlencode($address);
2015        $url = "https://maps.googleapis.com/maps/api/geocode/json?address={$encoded_address}&key={$api_key}";
2016
2017        $response = wp_remote_get($url, array(
2018            'timeout' => 10,
2019            'user-agent' => 'WordPress/TREB-Plugin'
2020        ));
2021
2022        if (is_wp_error($response)) {
2023            shift8_treb_log('Geocoding API error', array(
2024                'address' => esc_html($address),
2025                'error' => $response->get_error_message()
2026            ));
2027            return false;
2028        }
2029
2030        $response_code = wp_remote_retrieve_response_code($response);
2031        if ($response_code !== 200) {
2032            shift8_treb_log('Geocoding API HTTP error', array(
2033                'address' => esc_html($address),
2034                'response_code' => $response_code
2035            ));
2036            return false;
2037        }
2038
2039        $body = wp_remote_retrieve_body($response);
2040        $data = json_decode($body, true);
2041
2042        if (json_last_error() !== JSON_ERROR_NONE || !isset($data['status'])) {
2043            shift8_treb_log('Geocoding API invalid response', array(
2044                'address' => esc_html($address)
2045            ));
2046            return false;
2047        }
2048
2049        if ($data['status'] !== 'OK' || empty($data['results'])) {
2050            shift8_treb_log('Geocoding API no results', array(
2051                'address' => esc_html($address),
2052                'status' => $data['status']
2053            ));
2054            return false;
2055        }
2056
2057        // Extract coordinates
2058        $location = $data['results'][0]['geometry']['location'];
2059        $coordinates = array(
2060            'lat' => $location['lat'],
2061            'lng' => $location['lng']
2062        );
2063
2064        // Cache result for 24 hours
2065        set_transient($cache_key, $coordinates, DAY_IN_SECONDS);
2066
2067        shift8_treb_log('Address geocoded successfully', array(
2068            'address' => esc_html($address),
2069            'coordinates' => $coordinates
2070        ));
2071
2072        return $coordinates;
2073    }
